The paper is about a neural re-ranking model for ad-hoc search, which falls under the information retrieval (IR) field. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The model uses Transformer layers for contextualization, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the efficiency and effectiveness of the model, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper uses large-scale ranking collections, which could involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for image retrieval.
